<plot>Amid mass detentions and the mysterious disappearance of 48 refugees lost by the United Nations, displaced historically-warring African tribes unite through gospel music, faith, and an eerie Old Testament prophesy. ISAIAH'S CHILDREN's characters find themselves at the intersection between Middle Eastern and African politics. Their stories, previously unpublicized, are told with spirit, grace and - in the end - hope.</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?268991</url></doc>
